summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Lander Street, from Sixth Avenue South to Ninth Avenue South, all in the City of Seattle, by planking the same, in accordance with Resolution No. 465 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment," under the provisions of Ordinance No. 5693 of said city, approved December 6, 1899.
